HB 534 Original 2026 Regular Session Boyer
Abstract: Provides that bond or tax elections shall be held only during a regularly
scheduled primary election.
Present law provides that every bond, tax, or other election at which a proposition or
question is to be submitted to the voters shall be held only on the regularly scheduled spring
or fall election dates.
Proposed law retains present law as it applies to elections at which a proposition or question
is to be submitted to the voters. However, proposed law provides that bond or tax elections
shall be held only on the regularly scheduled primary election dates.
Effective if and when the proposed amendment of Article VI, Section 22 of the Constitution
of La. contained in the Act which originated as House Bill No. ____ of this 2026 R.S. of the
Legislature is adopted at a statewide election and becomes effective.
(Amends R.S. 18:402(F))
